occurrenceRemarks: Culms to 1.5-2 cm diam., to 5-6 m long, erect at base, scandent and hanging. Clumps more or less diffuse. Vegetative, many vigorous new shoots. Branching infravaginal; subsidiary branches rebranching, at least once geniculate; central branch often developing, at least at upper nodes, trailing. Young internodes glaucous. Culm leaves persistent, sheath abaxially smooth; blades erect, persistent.
